description:
Data & Insights Team of Sales Development & Efficiency Team is looking for a new member who will help us make data-driven business decisions.

Responsibilities:
Breaking down critical business data - gathering, cleaning, and analyzing crucial business data;
Interpreting the data - finding patterns and potential improvements in our reporting and business operations;
Sharing findings - designing and developing reporting solutions for key business stakeholders, including regional directors and the Board;
Active participation in data-driven HQ projects.

Tools you will use:
Looker Studio for creating interactive dashboards;
PowerBI for periodical reporting;
Google BigQuery as the primary data source;
Google Spreadsheets (+Big Query connector) and Google Slides: to perform ad hoc data analyses, blending data from our various reporting systems.

What we are looking for:
At least 2 years of professional experience with data analytics and/or business intelligence;
Strong data visualizations... skills - experience with at least one visualisation tool (e.g. Looker Studio or PowerBI);
SQL knowledge, ability to extract and manipulate data from relational databases - familiarity with Google BigQuery will be a plus;
Proactivity in problem-solving and ability to work with minimal supervision;
Fluency in Polish and English;
Strong willingness to develop in BI, Data Analytics, and Project Management areas.
Nice to have:
Prior exposure or familiarity with scripts (e.g., Python, JavaScript) will be a plus;
Previous experience in working with sales or marketing data will be a plus;
Bachelor’s degree or higher in a field of applied statistics/mathematics, economics, data science, engineering.

What we offer:
Great environment for the development of BI, Data Analytics, and Project Management skills;
Openness to test your ideas in the field of BI approach in our team;
Modern tech stack (Google Cloud Platform based solutions);
Remote or hybrid work model;
Attractive salary;
A unique opportunity to join an award-winning organization, one of the fastest-growing tech companies in Europe;
Involvement in critical projects in the RTB House headquarters;
Co-financing of external courses and training;
Co-financing of foreign language courses
